comments.body:
[~swathi] The vol-XXXXXXX-libvirt.xml is not getting migrated and this prevents the volume from being detached from the the migrated instance. 
{code}
2016-03-23 11:57:57 ERROR 000008230 read_vol_xml | i-c8abe249vol-21adf84d failed to read volume XML from /var/lib/eucalyptus/instances/work/AIDAAKGHGMJEBTKDFDZVM/i-c8abe249/vol-21adf84d-libvirt.xml
{code}
The  vol-XXXXXXX-libvirt.xml  is created in handlers_default.c -> doAttachVolume. When the instance is migrated and the volume is reattached we are just calling handlers_kvm.c ->  connect_ebs in  doMigrateInstances so the xml in not created.  I am not familiar with this code and would like suggestions on the best way to approach this?

[~swathi], this is the change that I am proposing
{code}
diff --git a/node/handlers_kvm.c b/node/handlers_kvm.c
index 7655017..912441d 100644
--- a/node/handlers_kvm.c
+++ b/node/handlers_kvm.c
@@ -758,6 +758,7 @@ static int doMigrateInstances(struct nc_state_t *nc, ncMetadata * pMeta, ncInsta
 {
     int ret = EUCA_OK;
     int credentials_prepared = 0;
+    char *libvirt_xml_modified = NULL;
 
     if (instancesLen <= 0) {
         LOGERROR("called with invalid instancesLen (%d)\n", instancesLen);
@@ -1001,6 +1002,10 @@ static int doMigrateInstances(struct nc_state_t *nc, ncMetadata * pMeta, ncInsta
                 }
                 // update the volume struct with connection string obtained from SC
                 euca_strncpy(volume->connectionString, vol_data->connect_string, sizeof(volume->connectionString));
+                // save volume info into vol-XXX-libvirt.xml for future detach
+                if (create_vol_xml(instance->instanceId, volume->volumeId, libvirt_xml, &libvirt_xml_modified) != EUCA_OK) {
+                    goto unroll;
+                }
 
                 continue;
 unroll:
{code}
The change is in dev-vasya-EUCA-12143
